{"ts":"2026-06-27T22:18:30.905Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"tool","toolName":"run_commands","toolCallId":"43oj067q","output":[{"query":"grep -rn \"seed\" package.json automation/tasks.json app/resources/developer-docs/dynamodb-schemas.ts 2>/dev/null || true","result":"package.json:13:    \"backend:seed\": \"cd backend && venv/bin/python app/seed.py\",\nautomation/tasks.json:824:    \"prompt\": \"This is the first task of Phase 5. Do not edit files. Audit the current project after Phase 4. Inspect the frontend stack, package.json, app routes, portal routes, admin routes, login pages, local auth preview utilities, local mock data, portal/admin components, docs from Phase 4, and any existing backend/API folders. Determine the safest MVP backend approach for this project. Default target architecture should be a separate local backend folder using FastAPI, SQLite, SQLAlchemy or SQLModel, Pydantic, password hashing, JWT auth, RBAC, and local dev CORS, unless the project already has a clearly better backend convention. Do not connect AWS, payment provider, object storage, real file upload, email, OTP provider, OAuth, SSO, or production auth. Do not add backend APIs for GFF AI tools such as Blueprint, ROI, Proposal, Sandbox, Marketplace, Foundry Studio, Talk to Agent, or Assessment. Produce a detailed gap report only. The gap report must cover backend folder needs, database choice, models, seed data, auth endpoints, RBAC roles, client portal CRUD APIs, admin CRUD APIs, frontend API client integration, route guards, migration strategy, local dev scripts, tests, documentation, risks, and exact implementation order. Do not edit files.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:840:    \"prompt\": \"Create a clean backend app structure for MVP development. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Suggested structure: backend/app/main.py, backend/app/core/config.py, backend/app/core/security.py, backend/app/core/rbac.py, backend/app/db/session.py, backend/app/db/base.py, backend/app/models, backend/app/schemas, backend/app/api/deps.py, backend/app/api/routes, backend/app/services, backend/app/seed.py. Keep it simple and understandable. Use FastAPI APIRouter. Keep all endpoints under /api/v1. Add /api/v1/health returning status ok and app name. Add error response helpers if useful. Do not overengineer. No AWS, no storage, no payment, no email, no OTP. Run basic backend import check if possible.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:848:    \"prompt\": \"Implement local SQLite database setup for the backend. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Use SQLAlchemy or SQLModel based on what is simplest and already available in the backend setup. Create engine/session dependency, Base metadata, init_db helper, and clear database URL config. Use a local SQLite file such as backend/dev.db by default and ensure it is ignored by git. Do not require external Postgres for MVP. Do not add migrations unless the backend already uses Alembic or the change is small and safe. For this MVP, create tables through init_db or seed script if simpler. Run backend import check or startup check if possible.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:891:    \"id\": \"131-phase5-seed-data-and-dev-users\",\nautomation/tasks.json:892:    \"title\": \"Create seed data and dev users\",\nautomation/tasks.json:894:    \"target\": \"seed data\",\nautomation/tasks.json:896:    \"prompt\": \"Create a safe local seed script for MVP backend. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Seed representative data only. Create dev users for roles: gff_admin, client_admin, client_member. Use simple documented local passwords such as password123 only in dev seed documentation. Create 2 to 3 representative client accounts, several projects, agent operations, documents metadata, invoices, support tickets, governance items. Do not use real client names or fake logos. Ensure seed script can be run repeatedly without duplicating data, either by checking existing emails/records or resetting safely with explicit command. Add README instructions. Run seed if safe and verify backend can start.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:904:    \"prompt\": \"Add simple local developer commands for running the backend and initializing data. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. If the repo root package.json exists, add safe scripts only if appropriate: backend:install, backend:dev, backend:seed, backend:check. Do not break existing scripts. Alternatively document commands in backend/README.md if adding root scripts is risky. Include command for starting FastAPI with uvicorn on localhost port 8000. Include command for seeding SQLite. Include environment setup using backend/.env.example. Run lint/build if frontend package scripts exist and backend check if possible.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:1136:    \"prompt\": \"Create or update docs/PHASE_5_MVP_BACKEND.md. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Document how to install backend dependencies, create .env from .env.example, initialize SQLite, run seed, start backend, start frontend, configure NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL, login with seeded dev users, and test portal/admin flows. Document that this phase is local/dev MVP only and does not include AWS, storage, payments, email, OTP, OAuth, SSO, production auth hardening, or backend for GFF AI tools. Include troubleshooting for CORS, missing DB, invalid token, and seed rerun. Run lint/build if docs affect build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:1144:    \"prompt\": \"Create or update docs/PHASE_5_SECURITY_LIMITATIONS.md. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Document MVP security limitations honestly: JWT in localStorage or dev storage, SQLite local DB, local seed users, no production password reset, no MFA, no refresh token hardening, no httpOnly secure cookie implementation unless already done, no rate limiting, no audit-grade logs, no production RBAC review, no file scanning, no payment compliance. Document required Phase 6 hardening steps: production database, httpOnly secure cookies or hardened session strategy, refresh token rotation, password reset, MFA/SSO optional, rate limiting, audit logs, secrets management, deployment config, CORS hardening. Run lint/build if docs affect build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:1152:    \"prompt\": \"Perform a local full-stack smoke QA for Phase 5. Do not add features unless fixing small clear issues. Verify backend can start, health endpoint works, database initializes, seed script works, dev users can login, /auth/me returns current user, client user cannot access admin APIs, admin user can access admin APIs, client portal dashboard fetches data, admin dashboard fetches data, support ticket create works, documents are metadata-only, invoices are metadata-only. Verify frontend builds. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Run available backend checks/tests and frontend lint/build. Fix only issues found during smoke QA.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:1168:    \"prompt\": \"Perform final QA for Phase 5. Do not add new features unless fixing a small clear issue. Verify local/dev backend exists and runs. Verify SQLite database setup. Verify seed data and dev users. Verify JWT login, auth/me, logout, RBAC, client data scoping, admin access. Verify CRUD APIs for clients, users, projects, AI operations, documents metadata, invoices metadata, support tickets, governance, dashboard summaries, analytics summaries. Verify frontend login connects to backend. Verify client portal pages use backend data: Dashboard, Projects, AI Operations, Documents, Billing, Support, Analytics, Governance, Activity, Settings. Verify admin pages use backend data: Dashboard, Clients, Users, Projects, AI Operations, Documents, Billing, Support, Analytics, Governance, Settings. Verify no AWS, storage, payment, email, OTP, OAuth, SSO, production auth, or backend for GFF AI tools was added. Verify landing page unchanged. Run backend tests/checks if available, backend startup/import checks, npm run lint, npm run build, npm run typecheck if available, and npm test if available. Final response must include pass/fail checklist, files changed, commands run, remaining warnings, local dev login credentials from seed docs, and TODOs for Phase 6 production hardening.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:1176:    \"prompt\": \"Audit the current Phase 5 implementation before AWS conversion. Do not edit files. Confirm that login, admin, client portal, local backend, SQLite models, JWT auth, RBAC, CRUD APIs, frontend API client, and portal/admin pages exist. Confirm GFF AI tools remain frontend-only and must not receive backend integration. Produce a short final implementation checklist only. Phase 6 must only move the MVP product from local SQLite to AWS DynamoDB and S3, connect document uploads/downloads, update env configuration, seed AWS data, and run final QA. Do not add new product features. Do not add payment, OTP, email, SSO, rate limiting, advanced security, audit logs, or backend for Blueprint, ROI, Proposal, Assessment, Sandbox, Marketplace, Foundry Studio, or Talk to Agent.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:1243:    \"id\": \"180-phase6-seed-aws-data\",\nautomation/tasks.json:1244:    \"title\": \"Create AWS DynamoDB seed script\",\nautomation/tasks.json:1246:    \"target\": \"AWS seed data\",\nautomation/tasks.json:1248:    \"prompt\": \"Create or update seed script to seed DynamoDB tables with final MVP data. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Seed users for gff_admin, client_admin, and client_member only. Seed 2 representative clients, projects, AI operations, document metadata, invoices, support tickets, and governance items. Do not seed fake real client names or logos. Document seed credentials in Phase 6 docs. Ensure seed can be safely rerun without duplicate records. Run seed only if environment is configured.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:1280:    \"prompt\": \"Create final concise handoff documentation. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Update docs/FINAL_MVP_HANDOFF.md with AWS tables, S3 bucket, env keys, seed users, local run commands, production run commands, frontend env, backend env, and final scope. Clearly state that GFF AI tools are frontend-only dummy/hardcoded and not backend-connected. Keep the document short and practical. Run build only if docs affect build.\"\n","success":true}],"durationMs":15}}
