SQLite and DynamoDB in `seed.py`. The focus is ensuring consistent, representative data. I'm focusing on the specified entities for both SQLite and DynamoDB. I'm focusing on \"Sovereign Logistics\" and the \"Supply Chain\" industry. I also have to implement neutral datasets for \"Client 2\". The script will use these neutral entities consistently.\n\n\n**Defining User Datasets**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on defining the user datasets, so I can integrate them into the seed script. I'll seed specific user roles: `gff_admin`, `client_admin`, and `client_member` with specific emails, full names, roles, and client IDs, according to the requirements. I've chosen `password123` for simplicity and documentation. Finally, I'll define 2 representative projects.\n\n\n**Constructing Project & AI Data**\n\nI'm expanding the seed data, to include two projects with client IDs 1 and 2, which I will link to their respective clients. I'm now designing two representative AI operations, one for each client/project, including all required fields. I've also incorporated basic document metadata for each client/project, to round out the neutral dataset.\n\n```text\nOkay, I've got a plan to ensure the seed script hits all the necessary fields, exactly as specified by the schema, and consistently used throughout the frontend and backend. I'm starting by designing a concise internal plan, just to keep everything organized.\n\nI'm now focusing on defining the internal design plan. My narrative centers on building a robust, production-ready DynamoDB seeding script for GFF, supporting both SQLite and DynamoDB, and initialized with realistic data for varied environments. Visualizing this as structured, verbose CLI output is key. I'll also update the documentation for clarity, too.\n\nI've just confirmed that the DynamoDB seeding is inherently safe from duplication. Utilizing `put_item` ensures overwriting existing items based on primary keys (like `email`, `client_id`, or `PK` and `SK`), effectively eliminating duplicate entries. This approach addresses the rerun safety requirement directly. I'm focusing on the script rewrite now, primarily for the `seed.py` file, so the databases are always properly seeded.\n\nOkay, I'm diving into the existing `backend/app/seed.py` file to understand the current seeding process and dependencies. I've confirmed that the script is run with `venv/bin/python`, which means we have existing Python dependencies in the virtual environment that can be used. Now I'm working to design a combined seeding block within `seed.py` that can efficiently manage both SQLite (via SQLAlchemy) and DynamoDB (using boto3). Currently I'm noting the existing seed data, and realizing I need to adjust client names and users to better match the task requirements.\n\nI'm now implementing the plan for neutral datasets across SQLite and DynamoDB in `seed.py`. The focus is ensuring consistent, representative data. I'm focusing on the specified entities for both SQLite and DynamoDB. I'm focusing on \"Sovereign Logistics\" and the \"Supply Chain\" industry. I also have to implement neutral datasets for \"Client 2\". The script will use these neutral entities consistently.\n\nI'm now zeroing in on defining the user datasets, so I can integrate them into the seed script. I'll seed specific user roles: `gff_admin`, `client_admin`, and `client_member` with specific emails, full names, roles, and client IDs, according to the requirements. I've chosen `password123` for simplicity and documentation. Finally, I'll define 2 representative projects.\n\nI'm expanding the seed data, to include two projects with client IDs 1 and 2, which I will link to their respective clients. I'm now designing two representative AI operations, one for each client/project, including all required fields. I've also incorporated basic document metadata for each client/project, to round out the neutral dataset.\n```\n\n**Adding Representative Records**\n\nI'm now adding realistic records to the seed data within the script, starting with document metadata and invoices, which are representative of real-world use cases. I'm focusing on \"Sovereign AI Security Blueprint\" and \"Ledger Integration Compliance Standard\", with appropriate fields for each. I've also added two invoices with various statuses and amounts. Finally, I'm constructing two support tickets with different priorities and assignments, to reflect diverse operational scenarios.\n\n\n**Constructing Governance Items**\n\nI'm now integrating representative governance items into the seeding script for both Client 1 and Client 2.  I'm focusing on defining `entity_type` fields in SQLite, given that it's a standard SQL model, and designing the key-value schema for DynamoDB.  These items include risk audits and compliance checks, with associated severity levels and statuses, for each of the two clients.\n\n\n**Designing DynamoDB Integration**\n\nI'm now determining how best to integrate DynamoDB seeding within `seed.py`. The focus is on reusing existing SQLite model structures to guide DynamoDB item definitions, maintaining data consistency. I'm carefully reviewing the schema for each entity in `backend/app/models/` to create a DynamoDB-specific seeding function. I'm going to keep the existing SQLite seeding code, and add `seed_dynamodb()` to support our new database. I'm also planning to update `seed_mock_database()` to align.\n\nI'm starting by inspecting the `backend/app/models/` directory for fields in `ClientAccount`, `Project`, and `User`. I'm going to read the contents of the Python files using `read_files`. I'm starting by reviewing and implementing my plan to seed a DynamoDB database, alongside the current, working SQLite seeding. I've noted that SQLite seeding currently succeeds, and so I should focus on the new database. I'll construct a new function to do the seeding. I've also identified I need to update the mock database seeding function.\n\n\n**Refining DynamoDB Integration**\n\nI'm now focusing on a complete overhaul of the seeding process. I'm updating `seed_mock_database()` in `dynamodb_client.py` for consistent mock data. I'll define a robust function in `seed.py` to directly seed AWS DynamoDB, ensuring schema adherence. I'm building a concise and elegant replacement for `seed.py`.\n\nI'm constructing the final data structure, and planning how to populate it for consistent seeding. The data structure will include Client entities with accompanying User roles: `gff_admin`, `client_admin`, `client_member`.\n\n\n**Defining Seed Script Logic**\n\nI'm now implementing the seeding logic with the various database options. I've designed the data structure for consistent seeding, including `gff_admin`, `client_admin`, and `client_member` roles. I'm implementing SQLite seeding if it's the configured database. I'm also implementing DynamoDB seeding based on environment variables for AWS keys.\n\n\n**Implementing Conditional Database Seeding**\n\nI'm now incorporating conditional logic into the seed script. My goal is to ensure DynamoDB seeding only runs if AWS credentials are provided, avoiding errors in local environments. If not configured, the script will gracefully skip DynamoDB and complete SQLite seeding, as I just reviewed. I'm also ensuring the seed script checks DynamoDB table attributes. I need to make sure the primary key is `email`, and verify each attribute, so I'll review `docs/PHASE_6_AWS_FINAL_SETUP.md` and `dynamodb-schemas.ts`.\n\n\n**Validating Table Attributes**\n\nI'm now implementing table attribute validation within the seed script to ensure data integrity and prevent errors. I'm focusing on verifying primary keys and data types against the specified schemas for both DynamoDB and SQLite. I'm checking that the `email` key in the `User` table, for instance, aligns. I've also begun to implement the plan to conditionally seed based on environment variables.\n\nI'm focusing on the `User` table, to make sure I am writing the correct `PK` and `SK` values. Then, I'll focus on the `client_id` for the `GFF_CLIENTS` table. I've noted that SQLite seeding currently succeeds, so I'll focus on the data for DynamoDB.\n\n\n**Adding AI Operations Details**\n\nI'm now incorporating detailed AI operation data, including the necessary fields like `id`, `client_id`, `project_id`, `name`, `agent_type`, `status`, `health`, `owner`, `governance_status`, and `entity_type`. These will be linked to the appropriate clients and projects within the seed script. I'm also ensuring that the timestamps adhere to the specified ISO 8601 format for consistency.\n\n\n**Populating Project Metadata**\n\nI'm now populating the seed script with detailed metadata for projects.  I'm adding invoice data with invoice numbers, statuses, amounts, and currency. Additionally, I'm incorporating support tickets with priorities and assignments, to reflect diverse project scenarios.  My primary focus is the `backend/app/seed.py` file, incorporating all necessary fields for representative data.\n\n\n\n**Integrating Governance Items**\n\nI'm now integrating the provided data into my seeding script. I've focused on creating and integrating records for \"Enclave Handshake Connection Refused\" and a governance item, ensuring all required fields are included for the data in a standardized, schema-compliant format. I'm double-checking the timestamp format.\n\n\n**Standardizing Schema Compatibility**\n\nI'm now ensuring complete database consistency by standardizing the seeded data across SQLite and DynamoDB. I'm focusing on making both seed paths identical in `seed.py`, using the same generic, representative clients, and records. This guarantees a clean, consistent MVP dataset regardless of the chosen database environment. I'm updating the SQLite models to ensure the seeding logic is aligned.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T22:21:15.946Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"tlrx94lv","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/backend/app/seed.py","old_text":null,"new_text":"import sys, os, datetime, argparse\nsys.path.append(os.path.dirname(os.path.dirname(os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__)))))\n\nimport boto3\nfrom sqlalchemy.orm import Session\nfrom backend.app.db import SessionLocal, init_db\nfrom backend.app.core.config import settings\nfrom backend.app.core.security import hash_password\nfrom backend.app.services.auth import AuthService\nfrom backend.app.services.logger import SystemLoggerService\nfrom backend.app.schemas.user import UserCreate\nfrom backend.app.schemas.system_log import SystemLogCreate\nfrom backend.app.models import (\n    User, ClientAccount, Project, AgentOperation,\n    DocumentItem, Invoice, SupportTicket, GovernanceItem, SystemLog\n)\n\n# Generic representative data for absolute compliance with GFF guidelines\nSEED_CLIENTS = [\n    {\n        \"id\": 1,\n        \"name\": \"Sovereign Logistics Corp\",\n        \"industry\": \"Supply Chain\",\n        \"region\": \"North America\",\n        \"status\": \"active\",\n        \"account_owner\": \"GFF Partner Team\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"id\": 2,\n        \"name\": \"Enterprise Grid Corp\",\n        \"industry\": \"Energy\",\n        \"region\": \"Europe\",\n        \"status\": \"active\",\n        \"account_owner\": \"GFF Partner Team\"\n    }\n]\n\nSEED_USERS = [\n    {\n        \"email\": \"gff_admin@gff.ai\",\n        \"password\": \"password123\",\n        \"full_name\": \"GFF Admin Lead\",\n        \"role\": \"gff_admin\",\n        \"client_id\": None\n    },\n    {\n        \"email\": \"client_admin@gff.ai\",\n        \"password\": \"password123\",\n        \"full_name\": \"Enterprise Admin Lead\",\n        \"role\": \"client_admin\",\n        \"client_id\": 1\n    },\n    {\n        \"email\": \"client_member@gff.ai\",\n        \"password\": \"password123\",\n        \"full_name\": \"Enterprise Analyst\",\n        \"role\": \"client_member\",\n        \"client_id\": 1\n    }\n]\n\ndef get_seed_projects(now):\n    return [\n        {\n            \"id\": 1,\n            \"client_id\": 1,\n            \"name\": \"Project Sovereign Mesh\",\n            \"phase\": \"Phase 1: Foundation\",\n            \"status\": \"active\",\n            \"health\": \"green\",\n            \"owner\": \"GFF Partner Team\",\n            \"progress\": 45,\n            \"description\": \"Deploying foundation for distributed agent meshes.\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": 2,\n            \"client_id\": 2,\n            \"name\": \"Project Ledger Compliance\",\n            \"phase\": \"Phase 3: Integration\",\n            \"status\": \"active\",\n            \"health\": \"amber\",\n            \"owner\": \"GFF Partner Team\",\n            \"progress\": 75,\n            \"description\": \"Integrating automated compliance controls.\"\n        }\n    ]\n\ndef get_seed_ops():\n    return [\n        {\n            \"id\": 1,\n            \"client_id\": 1,\n            \"project_id\": 1,\n            \"name\": \"SovereignMeshAgent\",\n            \"agent_type\": \"Distributed Mesh Orchestration\",\n            \"status\": \"active\",\n            \"health\": \"healthy\",\n            \"owner\": \"system\",\n            \"governance_status\": \"compliant\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": 2,\n            \"client_id\": 2,\n            \"project_id\": 2,\n            \"name\": \"LedgerAuditAgent\",\n            \"agent_type\": \"Automated Audit & Compliance\",\n            \"status\": \"active\",\n            \"health\": \"healthy\",\n            \"owner\": \"system\",\n            \"governance_status\": \"compliant\"\n        }\n    ]\n\ndef get_seed_docs(now):\n    return [\n        {\n            \"id\": 1,\n            \"client_id\": 1,\n            \"project_id\": 1,\n            \"title\": \"Sovereign AI Security Blueprint\",\n            \"filename\": \"sovereign_ai_security_blueprint.pdf\",\n            \"document_type\": \"Architecture Guide\",\n            \"visibility\": \"private\",\n            \"status\": \"active\",\n            \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n            \"owner\": \"security_officer\",\n            \"sha256\": \"0x\" + \"0\" * 64,\n            \"fileSize\": \"2.4 MB\",\n            \"description\": \"Cryptographically secured enclave system documentation and guidelines.\",\n            \"lastUpdated\": now.isoformat()\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": 2,\n            \"client_id\": 2,\n            \"project_id\": 2,\n            \"title\": \"Ledger Integration Compliance Standard\",\n            \"filename\": \"ledger_integration_compliance_standard.pdf\",\n            \"document_type\": \"Regulatory Specification\",\n            \"visibility\": \"private\",\n            \"status\": \"active\",\n            \"version\": \"1.1.0\",\n            \"owner\": \"compliance_lead\",\n            \"sha256\": \"0x\" + \"0\" * 64,\n            \"fileSize\": \"1.8 MB\",\n            \"description\": \"Audit trails and regulatory schema specifications.\",\n            \"lastUpdated\": now.isoformat()\n        }\n    ]\n\ndef get_seed_invoices(now):\n    return [\n        {\n            \"id\": 1,\n            \"client_id\": 1,\n            \"project_id\": 1,\n            \"invoice_number\": \"INV-2026-001\",\n            \"status\": \"paid\",\n            \"amount\": 150000.0,\n            \"currency\": \"USD\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": 2,\n            \"client_id\": 2,\n            \"project_id\": 2,\n            \"invoice_number\": \"INV-2026-002\",\n            \"status\": \"outstanding\",\n            \"amount\": 95000.0,\n            \"currency\": \"USD\"\n        }\n    ]\n\ndef get_seed_tickets():\n    return [\n        {\n            \"id\": 1,\n            \"client_id\": 1,\n            \"project_id\": 1,\n            \"title\": \"Enclave Handshake Connection Refused\",\n            \"category\": \"Technical\",\n            \"priority\": \"critical\",\n            \"status\": \"resolved\",\n            \"assigned_to\": \"support_team\",\n            \"created_by\": \"client_admin\",\n            \"description\": \"Secure enclave reported handshake timeout during high-frequency telemetry load testing.\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": 2,\n            \"client_id\": 2,\n            \"project_id\": 2,\n            \"title\": \"Fine-Tuning Data Format Validation\",\n            \"category\": \"Feature Request\",\n            \"priority\": \"medium\",\n            \"status\": \"open\",\n            \"assigned_to\": \"support_team\",\n            \"created_by\": \"client_admin\",\n            \"description\": \"Requesting schema validation templates for incremental model training pipelines.\"\n        }\n    ]\n\ndef get_seed_gov():\n    return [\n        {\n            \"id\": 1,\n            \"client_id\": 1,\n            \"project_id\": 1,\n            \"title\": \"Autonomous Agent Risk Audit\",\n            \"severity\": \"high\",\n            \"status\": \"active\",\n            \"owner\": \"risk_officer\",\n            \"description\": \"Continuous evaluation and drift checking of decision boundaries for regulatory compliance.\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"id\": 2,\n            \"client_id\": 2,\n            \"project_id\": 2,\n            \"title\": \"Key Rotation & Access Audit\",\n            \"severity\": \"critical\",\n            \"status\": \"resolved\",\n            \"owner\": \"compliance_lead\",\n            \"description\": \"Enforcement of automated 90-day integration token rotations across auditing endpoints.\"\n        }\n    ]\n\ndef seed_db(reset: bool = False):\n    print(\"--------------------------------------------------\")\n    print(\"      SEEDING GFF PLATFORM SYSTEM DATA             \")\n    print(\"--------------------------------------------------\")\n    \n    # 1. Seed SQLite Database\n    print(\"Initializing SQLite database...\")\n    init_db()\n    db = SessionLocal()\n    \n    now = datetime.datetime.utcnow()\n    \n    try:\n        if reset:\n            print(\"Wiping existing SQLite tables for clean slate...\")\n            for model in [SystemLog, SupportTicket, GovernanceItem, Invoice, DocumentItem, AgentOperation, User, Project, ClientAccount]:\n                db.query(model).delete()\n            db.commit()\n\n        # Seed SQLite Clients\n        clients_map = {}\n        for c in SEED_CLIENTS:\n            existing = db.query(ClientAccount).filter_by(id=c[\"id\"]).first()\n            if not existing:\n                existing = ClientAccount(\n                    id=c[\"id\"],\n                    name=c[\"name\"],\n                    industry=c[\"industry\"],\n                    region=c[\"region\"],\n                    account_owner=c[\"account_owner\"]\n                )\n                db.add(existing)\n                db.commit()\n                db.refresh(existing)\n            clients_map[c[\"id\"]] = existing\n\n        # Seed SQLite Users\n        for u in SEED_USERS:\n            existing = db.query(User).filter_by(email=u[\"email\"]).first()\n            if not existing:\n                print(f\"Creating SQLite User: {u['email']} ({u['role']})\")\n                AuthService.create_user(\n                    db, \n                    UserCreate(\n                        email=u[\"email\"], \n                        password=u[\"password\"], \n                        full_name=u[\"full_name\"], \n                        role=u[\"role\"], \n                        client_id=u[\"client_id\"]\n                    )\n                )\n                # Ensure the client ID is explicitly saved in case of any schema validation issues\n                user = db.query(User).filter_by(email=u[\"email\"]).first()\n                user.client_id = u[\"client_id\"]\n                user.name = u[\"full_name\"]\n                db.add(user)\n                db.commit()\n            else:\n                existing.hashed_password = hash_password(u[\"password\"])\n                existing.client_id = u[\"client_id\"]\n                existing.name = u[\"full_name\"]\n                existing.full_name = u[\"full_name\"]\n                existing.role = u[\"role\"]\n                db.add(existing)\n                db.commit()\n\n        # Seed SQLite Projects\n        projects_map = {}\n        for p in get_seed_projects(now):\n            existing = db.query(Project).filter_by(id=p[\"id\"]).first()\n            if not existing:\n                existing = Project(\n                    id=p[\"id\"],\n                    client_id=p[\"client_id\"],\n                    name=p[\"name\"],\n                    phase=p[\"phase\"],\n                    status=p[\"status\"],\n                    health=p[\"health\"],\n                    owner=p[\"owner\"],\n                    progress=p[\"progress\"],\n                    description=p[\"description\"]\n                )\n                db.add(existing)\n                db.commit()\n                db.refresh(existing)\n            projects_map[p[\"id\"]] = existing\n\n        # Seed SQLite AI Operations\n        for o in get_seed_ops():\n            existing = db.query(AgentOperation).filter_by(id=o[\"id\"]).first()\n            if not existing:\n                db.add(AgentOperation(\n                    id=o[\"id\"],\n                    client_id=o[\"client_id\"],\n                    project_id=o[\"project_id\"],\n                    name=o[\"name\"],\n                    agent_type=o[\"agent_type\"],\n                    status=o[\"status\"],\n                    health=o[\"health\"],\n                    owner=o[\"owner\"],\n                    governance_status=o[\"governance_status\"]\n                ))\n\n        # Seed SQLite Documents Metadata\n        for d in get_seed_docs(now):\n            existing = db.query(DocumentItem).filter_by(id=d[\"id\"]).first()\n            if not existing:\n                db.add(DocumentItem(\n                    id=d[\"id\"],\n                    client_id=d[\"client_id\"],\n                    project_id=d[\"project_id\"],\n                    title=d[\"title\"],\n                    filename=d[\"filename\"],\n                    document_type=d[\"document_type\"],\n                    visibility=d[\"visibility\"],\n                    status=d[\"status\"],\n                    version=d[\"version\"],\n                    owner=d[\"owner\"]\n                ))\n\n        # Seed SQLite Invoices\n        for i in get_seed_invoices(now):\n            existing = db.query(Invoice).filter_by(id=i[\"id\"]).first()\n            if not existing:\n                db.add(Invoice(\n                    id=i[\"id\"],\n                    client_id=i[\"client_id\"],\n                    project_id=i[\"project_id\"],\n                    invoice_number=i[\"invoice_number\"],\n                    status=i[\"status\"],\n                    amount=i[\"amount\"],\n                    currency=i[\"currency\"],\n                    due_date=now + datetime.timedelta(days=30)\n                ))\n\n        # Seed SQLite Support Tickets\n        for t in get_seed_tickets():\n            existing = db.query(SupportTicket).filter_by(id=t[\"id\"]).first()\n            if not existing:\n                db.add(SupportTicket(\n                    id=t[\"id\"],\n                    client_id=t[\"client_id\"],\n                    project_id=t[\"project_id\"],\n                    title=t[\"title\"],\n                    category=t[\"category\"],\n                    priority=t[\"priority\"],\n                    status=t[\"status\"],\n                    assigned_to=t[\"assigned_to\"],\n                    created_by=t[\"created_by\"],\n                    description=t[\"description\"]\n                ))\n\n        # Seed SQLite Governance Items\n        for g in get_seed_gov():\n            existing = db.query(GovernanceItem).filter_by(id=g[\"id\"]).first()\n            if not existing:\n                db.add(GovernanceItem(\n                    id=g[\"id\"],\n                    client_id=g[\"client_id\"],\n                    project_id=g[\"project_id\"],\n                    title=g[\"title\"],\n                    severity=g[\"severity\"],\n                    status=g[\"status\"],\n                    owner=g[\"owner\"],\n                    due_date=now + datetime.timedelta(days=15),\n                    description=g[\"description\"]\n                ))\n\n        db.commit()\n        \n        SystemLoggerService.create_log(\n            db,\n            SystemLogCreate(\n                level=\"INFO\",\n                message=\"SQLite database seeded with compliant GFF representative entities.\",\n                module=\"system_init\"\n            )\n        )\n        print(\"SQLite seeding completed successfully.\")\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"Error seeding SQLite database: {e}\")\n    finally:\n        db.close()\n\n    # 2. Seed AWS DynamoDB Tables if Environment is Configured\n    seed_aws_dynamodb()\n\ndef seed_aws_dynamodb():\n    print(\"--------------------------------------------------\")\n    print(\"      SEEDING AWS DYNAMODB TABLES                 \")\n    print(\"--------------------------------------------------\")\n    \n    # Run seed only if environment is configured\n    aws_access_key = os.getenv(\"AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID\") or getattr(settings, \"AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID\", \"\")\n    aws_secret_key = os.getenv(\"AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY\") or getattr(settings, \"AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY\", \"\")\n    region = os.getenv(\"AWS_REGION\") or getattr(settings, \"AWS_REGION\", \"us-east-1\")\n    \n    is_configured = (\n        aws_access_key and \"placeholder\" not in aws_access_key and len(aws_access_key.strip()) > 10 and\n        aws_secret_key and \"placeholder\" not in aws_secret_key and len(aws_secret_key.strip()) > 10\n    )\n    \n    if not is_configured:\n        print(\"[DYNAMODB_SEED] AWS environment keys are not configured. Skipping AWS DynamoDB seeding.\")\n        return False\n\n    print(f\"[DYNAMODB_SEED] Detected configured AWS environment in {region}. Checking DynamoDB connection...\")\n    try:\n        dynamodb = boto3.resource(\n            \"dynamodb\",\n            region_name=region,\n            aws_access_key_id=aws_access_key,\n            aws_secret_access_key=aws_secret_key\n        )\n        \n        # Access tables specified in settings\n        users_table = dynamodb.Table(settings.DYNAMODB_USERS_TABLE)\n        clients_table = dynamodb.Table(settings.DYNAMODB_CLIENTS_TABLE)\n        items_table = dynamodb.Table(settings.DYNAMODB_ITEMS_TABLE)\n        \n        # Verify connectivity by checking table status\n        users_table.table_status\n        clients_table.table_status\n        items_table.table_status\n        print(\"[DYNAMODB_SEED] Successfully connected to AWS DynamoDB.\")\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"[DYNAMODB_SEED] Error connecting to AWS DynamoDB: {e}. Cannot perform AWS seeding.\")\n        return False\n\n    now = datetime.datetime.utcnow()\n    hashed_pass = hash_password(\"password123\")\n    \n    # A. Seed GFF_USERS Table\n    print(f\"[DYNAMODB_SEED] Seeding GFF_USERS table ({settings.DYNAMODB_USERS_TABLE})...\")\n    for u in SEED_USERS:\n        item = {\n            \"email\": u[\"email\"],\n            \"hashed_password\": hashed_pass,\n            \"full_name\": u[\"full_name\"],\n            \"name\": u[\"full_name\"],\n            \"role\": u[\"role\"],\n            \"status\": \"active\",\n            \"client_id\": str(u[\"client_id\"]) if u[\"client_id\"] is not None else None,\n            \"is_active\": True,\n            \"id\": u[\"client_id\"] or 1,\n            \"created_at\": now.isoformat(),\n            \"updated_at\": now.isoformat()\n        }\n        users_table.put_item(Item=item)\n        print(f\"  -> Seeded User: {u['email']}\")\n\n    # B. Seed GFF_CLIENTS Table\n    print(f\"[DYNAMODB_SEED] Seeding GFF_CLIENTS table ({settings.DYNAMODB_CLIENTS_TABLE})...\")\n    for c in SEED_CLIENTS:\n        item = {\n            \"client_id\": str(c[\"id\"]),\n            \"name\": c[\"name\"],\n            \"company_name\": c[\"name\"],\n            \"industry\": c[\"industry\"],\n            \"region\": c[\"region\"],\n            \"status\": c[\"status\"],\n            \"account_owner\": c[\"account_owner\"],\n            \"created_at\": now.isoformat()\n        }\n        clients_table.put_item(Item=item)\n        print(f\"  -> Seeded Client: {c['name']}\")\n\n    # C. Seed GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS Table\n    print(f\"[DYNAMODB_SEED] Seeding GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS single-table ({settings.DYNAMODB_ITEMS_TABLE})...\")\n    \n    # C1. Projects\n    for p in get_seed_projects(now):\n        item = {\n            \"PK\": f\"CLIENT#{p['client_id']}\",\n            \"SK\": f\"PROJ#{p['id']}\",\n            \"GSI1PK\": f\"PROJ#{p['id']}\",\n            \"GSI1SK\": \"METADATA\",\n            \"id\": p[\"id\"],\n            \"client_id\": str(p[\"client_id\"]),\n            \"name\": p[\"name\"],\n            \"phase\": p[\"phase\"],\n            \"status\": p[\"status\"],\n            \"health\": p[\"health\"],\n            \"owner\": p[\"owner\"],\n            \"progress\": p[\"progress\"],\n            \"description\": p[\"description\"],\n            \"entity_type\": \"PROJECT\",\n            \"created_at\": now.isoformat()\n        }\n        items_table.put_item(Item=item)\n        print(f\"  -> Seeded Project: {p['name']}\")\n\n    # C2. AI Operations\n    for o in get_seed_ops():\n        item = {\n            \"PK\": f\"CLIENT#{o['client_id']}\",\n            \"SK\": f\"AIOPS#{o['id']}\",\n            \"GSI1PK\": f\"PROJ#{o['project_id']}\",\n            \"GSI1SK\": f\"AIOPS#{o['id']}\",\n            \"id\": o[\"id\"],\n            \"client_id\": str(o[\"client_id\"]),\n            \"project_id\": str(o[\"project_id\"]),\n            \"name\": o[\"name\"],\n            \"agent_type\": o[\"agent_type\"],\n            \"status\": o[\"status\"],\n            \"health\": o[\"health\"],\n            \"owner\": o[\"owner\"],\n            \"governance_status\": o[\"governance_status\"],\n            \"entity_type\": \"AI_OPERATION\",\n            \"created_at\": now.isoformat()\n        }\n        items_table.put_item(Item=item)\n        print(f\"  -> Seeded AI Operation: {o['name']}\")\n\n    # C3. Document Metadata\n    for d in get_seed_docs(now):\n        item = {\n            \"PK\": f\"CLIENT#{d['client_id']}\",\n            \"SK\": f\"DOC#{d['id']}\",\n            \"GSI1PK\": f\"PROJ#{d['project_id']}\",\n            \"GSI1SK\": f\"DOC#{d['id']}\",\n            \"id\": d[\"id\"],\n            \"client_id\": str(d[\"client_id\"]),\n            \"project_id\": str(d[\"project_id\"]),\n            \"title\": d[\"title\"],\n            \"filename\": d[\"filename\"],\n            \"document_type\": d[\"document_type\"],\n            \"visibility\": d[\"visibility\"],\n            \"status\": d[\"status\"],\n            \"version\": d[\"version\"],\n            \"owner\": d[\"owner\"],\n            \"sha256\": d[\"sha256\"],\n            \"fileSize\": d[\"fileSize\"],\n            \"description\": d[\"description\"],\n            \"lastUpdated\": d[\"lastUpdated\"],\n            \"entity_type\": \"DOCUMENT\",\n            \"created_at\": now.isoformat()\n        }\n        items_table.put_item(Item=item)\n        print(f\"  -> Seeded Document: {d['title']}\")\n\n    # C4. Invoices\n    for i in get_seed_invoices(now):\n        item = {\n            \"PK\": f\"CLIENT#{i['client_id']}\",\n            \"SK\": f\"INV#{i['id']}\",\n            \"GSI1PK\": \"BILLING_PERIOD#2026_06\",\n            \"GSI1SK\": f\"INV#{i['id']}\",\n            \"id\": i[\"id\"],\n            \"client_id\": str(i[\"client_id\"]),\n            \"project_id\": str(i[\"project_id\"]),\n            \"invoice_number\": i[\"invoice_number\"],\n            \"status\": i[\"status\"],\n            \"amount\": i[\"amount\"],\n            \"currency\": i[\"currency\"],\n            \"entity_type\": \"INVOICE\",\n            \"created_at\": now.isoformat()\n        }\n        items_table.put_item(Item=item)\n        print(f\"  -> Seeded Invoice: {i['invoice_number']}\")\n\n    # C5. Support Tickets\n    for t in get_seed_tickets():\n        item = {\n            \"PK\": f\"CLIENT#{t['client_id']}\",\n            \"SK\": f\"TICKET#{t['id']}\",\n            \"GSI1PK\": f\"STATUS#{t['status'].upper()}\",\n            \"GSI1SK\": f\"TICKET#{t['id']}\",\n            \"id\": t[\"id\"],\n            \"client_id\": str(t[\"client_id\"]),\n            \"project_id\": str(t[\"project_id\"]),\n            \"title\": t[\"title\"],\n            \"category\": t[\"category\"],\n            \"priority\": t[\"priority\"],\n            \"status\": t[\"status\"],\n            \"assigned_to\": t[\"assigned_to\"],\n            \"created_by\": t[\"created_by\"],\n            \"description\": t[\"description\"],\n            \"entity_type\": \"SUPPORT\",\n            \"created_at\": now.isoformat()\n        }\n        items_table.put_item(Item=item)\n        print(f\"  -> Seeded Support Ticket: {t['title']}\")\n\n    # C6. Governance Items\n    for g in get_seed_gov():\n        item = {\n            \"PK\": f\"CLIENT#{g['client_id']}\",\n            \"SK\": f\"GOV#{g['id']}\",\n            \"GSI1PK\": \"STANDARD#EXTERNAL\",\n            \"GSI1SK\": f\"GOV#{g['id']}\",\n            \"id\": g[\"id\"],\n            \"client_id\": str(g[\"client_id\"]),\n            \"project_id\": str(g[\"project_id\"]),\n            \"title\": g[\"title\"],\n            \"severity\": g[\"severity\"],\n            \"status\": g[\"status\"],\n            \"owner\": g[\"owner\"],\n            \"description\": g[\"description\"],\n            \"entity_type\": \"GOVERNANCE\",\n            \"created_at\": now.isoformat()\n        }\n        items_table.put_item(Item=item)\n        print(f\"  -> Seeded Governance Item: {g['title']}\")\n\n    print(\"[DYNAMODB_SEED] AWS DynamoDB seeding completed successfully.\")\n    return True\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"Seed GFF AI Platform Datasets.\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--reset\", action=\"store_true\", help=\"Reset SQLite database before seeding.\")\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n    seed_db(reset=args.reset)\n"}}}
