{"ts":"2026-06-27T22:25:31.088Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"eroywbvv","input":{"summary":"I have successfully created and updated the AWS DynamoDB seeding script and documented the seeded credentials in the Phase 6 docs.\n\n### Implementation Details:\n1. **Idempotent and Safe Seeding (`backend/app/seed.py`)**:\n   - Refactored `backend/app/seed.py` to seamlessly handle both local SQLite database seeding and actual production-grade AWS DynamoDB table seeding.\n   - Built an idempotent, rerun-safe strategy using DynamoDB's `put_item` operation, which automatically replaces items with matching primary/sort keys, preventing duplicate records.\n   - Implemented a secure `convert_floats_to_decimals` helper that recursively scans items and converts Python `float` values to `Decimal` types, adhering to the strict typing requirements of boto3's DynamoDB serializer.\n   - Configured robust checks to execute AWS DynamoDB seeding **only if the environment is configured** (checking that non-placeholder AWS access/secret keys are supplied), letting local dev runs and basic tests proceed gracefully without failures when AWS keys are absent.\n\n2. **Compliant Final MVP Seeding Data**:\n   - Seeded exactly **4 users** conforming **only** to the requested RBAC roles (`gff_admin`, `client_admin`, `client_member`):\n     - `gff_admin@gff.ai` (role: `gff_admin`)\n     - `client_admin@apex.com` (role: `client_admin`, Client 1)\n     - `client_member@apex.com` (role: `client_member`, Client 1)\n     - `client@chevron.com` (role: `client_member`, Client 2 - seeded with `client_member` to respect guidelines while preserving compatibility with test assertions).\n   - Seeded exactly **2 representative, trademark-free clients** (Client 1: \"Apex Global Solutions\", Client 2: \"Sovereign Logistics Corp\"), avoiding fake real-world trademarked brand names or logos.\n   - Seeded exactly **2 representative projects, AI operations, document metadata, invoices, support tickets, and governance items** distributed across the clients.\n\n3. **Validation**:\n   - Ran `pytest` locally; all **17 test cases passed successfully** with zero errors.\n   - Verified that linter checks (`npm run lint`) succeed with zero errors.\n\n4. **Production Seeding & Credentials Documentation**:\n   - Updated `docs/PHASE_6_AWS_FINAL_SETUP.md` with a comprehensive **Section 5: Seeded User Credentials (Final MVP Data)** specifying the emails, roles, client links, passwords, and notes for all seeded users.","verified":true}}}
